SIGCSE 2012 Outstanding Contribution to Computer Science Education (<a href="Association_for_Computing_Machinery.html" title="Association for Computing Machinery">ACM</a>, 2012)</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Harold (Hal) Abelson</b> is a Professor of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MIT_Electrical_Engineering_and_Computer_Science_Department" title="MIT Electrical Engineering and Computer Science Department">Electrical Engineering and Computer Science</a> at <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology" title="Massachusetts Institute of Technology">MIT</a>, a fellow of the <a href="IEEE.html" title="IEEE" class="mw-redirect">IEEE</a>, and a founding director of both <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Creative_Commons" title="Creative Commons">Creative Commons</a> and the <a href="Free_Software_Foundation.html" title="Free Software Foundation">Free Software Foundation</a>.</p>
<p></p>
